Full recipe⬇️

Chicken Thighs

Onion powder 
Garlic powder 
Salt
Pepper 
Paprika 
Italian herbs 
Olive oil

Sauce 

2 tbsp Butter 
2 Tbsp fresh minced Garlic
1/3 cup Chicken broth
1/2 cup Heavy whipping cream
Sun dried Tomatoes 
1 Tbsp White cooking wine 
1/2 cup Fresh Shredded Parmesan or Italian cheese 
Red pepper flakes 
Salt 
Pepper 
Italian herbs 

Season & pansear Chicken thighs on both sides w/olive oil in skillet. Transfer to separate Pan. In same skillet start your sauce. Add butter & garlic, cook for about 3 mins. Add chicken broth, sun dried tomatoes and whipping cream. Add seasoning and allow to simmer. Add your cheese while constantly stirring. Pour sauce over chicken and bake in oven for 30-35min on 400 degrees. Serve over Mashed Potatoes ☺️

Steak Quesadillas 🔥 juicy Ribeye is always my go to😍 Full Recipe?

Update* Full Recipe⬇️

3 Ribeye Steaks
Salt & Pepper to taste 
Montreal Steak Seasoning 
3 Tbsp Avacado oil 
3 Tbsp butter 
3 garlic cloves 
1 red pepper sliced
1 green pepper sliced 
1 yellow onion sliced
Cilantro bunch 
Quesadilla cheese
Large flour Burrito Tortillas

Heat 1 Tbsp of Avacado oil in skillet, sauté peppers and onion. 
Remove and set aside. 
Season Ribeye on both sides. 
In same skillet add 2 Tbsp of Avacado oil. 
Pansear Ribeyes on both sides.
Add 3 Tbsp of butter and garlic cloves. 
Sear Ribeyes 4-5mins before removing. 
Slice into thin pieces before tossing back into skillet. (I like mines this way, feel free to skip that step) 
Add peppers to skillet of sliced Ribeyes. 

In separate pan add 1 Tbsp butter, add tortilla to skillet, add cheese, steak and pepper mix on top. Fold tortilla over and allow to cheeses to melt fully. Remove from skillet and slice. 
Enjoy w/green salsa, guacamole and sour cream❤️

Browned Butter Chewy Chocolate Chip Cookies🔥
Recipe⬇️ *Caption Updated* 

2 sticks of Butter
1 cup Brown Sugar 
1/2 cup granulated sugar 
1 Tsp vanilla extract 
2 eggs 
1/2 Tsp sea salt 
1 Tsp baking soda
2 & 1/4 cups All purpose flour
2 cups semisweet chocolate 

 Melt butter in pot on medium heat until butter is browned. Careful not to burn. Transfer to mixing bowl. Add Sugar and vanilla. Mix. Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour and baking soda and mix well. Cover and place in fridge for 1 hour. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Scoop and bake for 10-12 minutes or until golden brown.

Let’s discuss. Bananas or no bananas in the Banana Pudding? I’m team NO bananas 😭

Full Recipe ⬇️

2 Cups Granulated Sugar
4 Tbsp unbleached Flour
4 Egg Yolks
4 cups Evaporated Milk
2 Tsp Vanilla extract 
2 boxes Vanilla wafers 
1 Banana (don’t nobody got time for that) 

In medium saucepan, combine Sugar and flour. Mix ingredients. Add Egg Yolks and evaporated Milk. Mix well before adding to heat. Heat pan on medium heat and stir constantly. Careful not to allow custard to stick to pan. Continue stirring for about 5 minutes until it thickens. Remove from heat. Add vanilla extract. Allow to chill for 10 mins. 
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mix. Repeat steps. Cover & chill in fridge for 4 hours. Top with Whip cream once pudding is ready. Enjoy
